WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.560 --> 00:00:04.276
Confirmands, did you remember
any part of the Gospel?

00:00:04.276 --> 00:00:07.167
Jesus says something
there about some bread.

00:00:07.167 --> 00:00:08.820
Did you hear it?

00:00:11.670 --> 00:00:17.652
In the second part of the Gospel,
Jesus says, "Your fathers ate manna and

00:00:17.652 --> 00:00:24.062
died." Then He says about Himself, "I
am the living bread that came down from

00:00:24.062 --> 00:00:29.618
heaven; whoever eats this bread will
have life." Now, this is very important

00:00:29.618 --> 00:00:31.755
for you, confirmands, to remember.

00:00:32.435 --> 00:00:32.789
Why?

00:00:32.789 --> 00:00:35.978
Because on Saturday you receive
confirmation, and on Sunday

00:00:35.978 --> 00:00:38.458
half of you are not at Mass.

00:00:38.458 --> 00:00:41.646
This has already become a
tradition among our confirmands.

00:00:41.646 --> 00:00:47.670
And for you to understand why you need
to come on Sunday, I will now talk about

00:00:47.670 --> 00:00:50.858
the Holy Mass and this bread, what it is.

00:00:50.858 --> 00:00:53.338
So that Mass is not something boring.

00:00:53.338 --> 00:00:57.944
Because if you understand today what
Mass is, what Jesus says about this

00:00:57.944 --> 00:01:00.425
bread, you will come to Mass again.

00:01:01.955 --> 00:01:07.698
When God created the world, and
we know the first humans sinned,

00:01:07.698 --> 00:01:11.049
God sought a way to help them.

00:01:11.049 --> 00:01:17.750
He then chose the Israeli people and
wanted to lead them out of slavery.

00:01:17.750 --> 00:01:23.973
He made a covenant with them,
known as the Ark of the Covenant.

00:01:23.973 --> 00:01:29.238
While the Israeli people were freed
from slavery, they always carried

00:01:29.238 --> 00:01:35.940
this Ark of the Covenant with them,
just like you girls carry your purses.

00:01:36.880 --> 00:01:40.328
So, you always have something
important in your purse.

00:01:40.328 --> 00:01:44.160
The Israelites had the Ark
of the Covenant, which was

00:01:44.160 --> 00:01:45.693
very important to them.

00:01:45.693 --> 00:01:46.077
Why?

00:01:46.077 --> 00:01:49.142
Because it was a symbol of God's presence.

00:01:49.142 --> 00:01:53.357
And whenever they carried the
Ark of the Covenant, they won

00:01:53.357 --> 00:01:55.657
battles; no one could defeat them.

00:01:55.657 --> 00:02:00.255
What does this up here remind
you of, the tabernacle we call

00:02:00.255 --> 00:02:02.555
it, where the host is kept?

00:02:04.335 --> 00:02:09.221
It is also a symbol of God's
presence, and the living God is there.

00:02:09.221 --> 00:02:14.456
We store the particles of the host
there, and when we enter the church, we

00:02:14.456 --> 00:02:16.899
look at that tabernacle and worship it.

00:02:16.899 --> 00:02:20.738
A church that doesn't have
it, you don't even need to

00:02:20.738 --> 00:02:22.483
cross yourself when you enter.

00:02:22.483 --> 00:02:26.322
The most important thing is the
red light above, which signifies

00:02:26.322 --> 00:02:28.416
that the living God is present.

00:02:28.416 --> 00:02:34.350
And now you see, the Israelites gradually
came to see it as a good thing, so great.

00:02:34.470 --> 00:02:42.893
We carry that Ark, wherever we go we
win, no one can do anything to us, but

00:02:42.893 --> 00:02:46.857
the Lord didn't want it to be magical.

00:02:46.857 --> 00:02:52.308
He wanted that Covenant to be about
observing the Ten Commandments.

00:02:52.308 --> 00:02:59.245
And one of the things carried
in the Ark as a reminder of this

00:02:59.245 --> 00:03:03.704
were the stone tablets inscribed
with the Ten Commandments.

00:03:03.725 --> 00:03:06.576
And what was the problem?

00:03:06.576 --> 00:03:13.420
The Israelites quickly relied on God's
help, blessings, and victories, but they

00:03:13.420 --> 00:03:16.271
stopped keeping the Ten Commandments.

00:03:16.271 --> 00:03:23.685
Little by little, they began to mix
with pagans, and what happened then?

00:03:23.685 --> 00:03:24.825
Something terrible.

00:03:24.825 --> 00:03:27.107
They lost God's protection.

00:03:27.107 --> 00:03:32.810
Because God did not want
them to behave that way.

00:03:32.810 --> 00:03:36.417
The covenant was not
agreed upon like that.

00:03:36.417 --> 00:03:39.123
So, what happens to the confirmands?

00:03:39.123 --> 00:03:41.378
What happens to all Christians?

00:03:41.378 --> 00:03:46.339
Those who are baptized receive the
sacraments but keep the commandments.

00:03:46.339 --> 00:03:49.045
What is one of the commandments?

00:03:49.045 --> 00:03:54.457
That we come on Sundays to...
And you must not forget that.

00:03:54.457 --> 00:03:58.967
Because Jesus says that whoever
eats and drinks the body

00:03:58.967 --> 00:04:01.673
and blood has life in them.

00:04:01.673 --> 00:04:06.183
And God noticed how the Israelites
gradually started to distance

00:04:06.183 --> 00:04:08.889
themselves from Him in their hearts.

00:04:08.889 --> 00:04:16.104
And then He began to warn them, don't do
that, or misfortune will come upon you.

00:04:16.815 --> 00:04:19.544
No, they did not experience God.

00:04:19.544 --> 00:04:27.278
Just like many of the young people here in
the church, you who will become their age,

00:04:27.278 --> 00:04:33.647
we can live physically without God and the
Eucharist, but we are spiritually dead.

00:04:33.647 --> 00:04:40.017
We physically live, walk, but we are
greatly exposed to the influence of Satan.

00:04:40.017 --> 00:04:43.201
Now, I will explain step by step.

00:04:43.201 --> 00:04:48.661
So, when God saw that they were
drifting away, they started mingling

00:04:48.661 --> 00:04:55.030
with the pagan people, and they
carried the Ark of the Covenant as a

00:04:55.030 --> 00:04:57.760
magical object because it helped them.

00:04:58.780 --> 00:05:03.335
And then you have in the Book of
Revelation... Interestingly, the Ark

00:05:03.335 --> 00:05:05.992
of the New Covenant is mentioned again.

00:05:05.992 --> 00:05:11.686
You know, my young ones, that you have
the Bible, the Old and New Testament.

00:05:11.686 --> 00:05:13.583
You must have surpassed that.

00:05:13.583 --> 00:05:18.898
So, I was just talking about the Old
Covenant, and in Revelation, it talks

00:05:18.898 --> 00:05:21.555
about the New Ark of the Covenant.

00:05:21.555 --> 00:05:24.971
And that New Ark of the Covenant is Mary.

00:05:24.971 --> 00:05:25.730
Why Mary?

00:05:25.730 --> 00:05:26.490
Let's compare.

00:05:26.930 --> 00:05:34.045
So, at that time, the Ark of the
Covenant was made from the best wood,

00:05:34.045 --> 00:05:37.366
which in our language would be acacia.

00:05:37.366 --> 00:05:43.533
Acacia has unique sap and resin and
lasts a long time without rotting.

00:05:43.533 --> 00:05:50.174
They built the Ark of the Covenant
from this wood so it wouldn't decay.

00:05:50.174 --> 00:05:57.290
Mary, the Ark of the New Covenant, was
assumed into heaven and was not buried.

00:05:57.465 --> 00:06:00.119
Her gentle body did not decay.

00:06:00.119 --> 00:06:07.199
You see, the Ark of the New Covenant was
adorned by the Israelites with the finest

00:06:07.199 --> 00:06:12.508
gold, diamonds, everything they had,
while Mary is naturally a beautiful woman.

00:06:12.508 --> 00:06:17.818
Now we come to the core that
is most important to us.

00:06:17.818 --> 00:06:22.242
What did they carry in
the Ark of the Covenant?

00:06:22.242 --> 00:06:24.455
I already mentioned one thing.

00:06:24.455 --> 00:06:27.995
They carried the Ten
Commandments, as the Covenant.

00:06:28.455 --> 00:06:31.385
Do you guess what else they carried?

00:06:31.385 --> 00:06:32.641
A phone charger?

00:06:32.641 --> 00:06:38.084
What do you think was also in
the Ark of the Old Covenant?

00:06:38.084 --> 00:06:38.503
How?

00:06:38.503 --> 00:06:43.527
Hosts, you said hosts, not hosts,
but it was manna, you're close.

00:06:43.527 --> 00:06:49.807
So when God led His people through the
desert, He fed them with manna from

00:06:49.807 --> 00:06:51.900
heaven, which is unleavened bread.

00:06:51.900 --> 00:06:55.250
And as needed, He would send them bread.

00:06:55.630 --> 00:07:00.528
Along with the Ten Commandments, there
was that bread, and there was the

00:07:00.528 --> 00:07:05.050
staff, a symbol of Moses' priesthood,
which led them through the desert.

00:07:05.050 --> 00:07:10.325
However, when God warned them that they
had strayed, when He warned them to

00:07:10.325 --> 00:07:16.731
return, He told them that if they did not
return with their hearts and did not keep

00:07:16.731 --> 00:07:18.992
the commandments, they would all perish.

00:07:18.992 --> 00:07:21.630
And that is what happened to them.

00:07:22.065 --> 00:07:27.224
The Babylonians conquered them, destroyed
Jerusalem, and took them into captivity.

00:07:27.224 --> 00:07:31.446
However, a prophet named
Jeremiah managed to hide the

00:07:31.446 --> 00:07:34.260
Ark of the Covenant before that.

00:07:34.260 --> 00:07:38.951
You see, my dear ones,
they ended up in captivity.

00:07:38.951 --> 00:07:45.518
If you do not continue to nourish
yourselves with the body and blood of

00:07:45.518 --> 00:07:52.085
Jesus Christ, not just you confirmands,
but all of us, we fall into captivity—not

00:07:52.085 --> 00:07:54.900
physical, but the captivity of sin.

00:07:56.030 --> 00:08:01.805
Because anyone who does not have the
grace of the Holy Spirit and the strength

00:08:01.805 --> 00:08:04.500
given by the Eucharist cannot resist sin.

00:08:04.500 --> 00:08:07.195
And then we become slaves to sin.

00:08:07.195 --> 00:08:11.045
If the Babylonians destroyed the
Israelites and they fell into

00:08:11.045 --> 00:08:14.895
physical slavery, if we are not
nourished by spiritual food,

00:08:14.895 --> 00:08:17.590
we do not have life within us.

00:08:17.590 --> 00:08:20.285
The Devil will not leave us alone.

00:08:20.285 --> 00:08:24.905
He will draw you into various
sins, and then what are we?

00:08:25.405 --> 00:08:26.342
Spiritually dead.

00:08:26.342 --> 00:08:27.280
Spiritually dead.

00:08:27.280 --> 00:08:32.437
And you see how important
it is to understand what is

00:08:32.437 --> 00:08:34.781
happening here at the altar.

00:08:34.781 --> 00:08:37.125
How important the Eucharist is.

00:08:37.125 --> 00:08:39.000
Why is it important?

00:08:39.000 --> 00:08:45.564
Maybe some of you, maybe even your parents
or godparents, because they aren't, I

00:08:45.564 --> 00:08:50.721
heard confessions yesterday, they aren't
great examples either, because, don't take

00:08:50.721 --> 00:08:57.285
it the wrong way, but children look up
to their father, mother, and godparents.

00:08:57.604 --> 00:09:01.125
If they don't go to Mass, then
you can't expect your child to go.

00:09:03.805 --> 00:09:08.192
So, it's important to
understand what happens at Mass.

00:09:08.192 --> 00:09:14.530
Many will say, "I won't go to Mass
because there are gays, pedophiles.

00:09:14.530 --> 00:09:20.867
That priest is boring, that one is
old, that one doesn't know..." You

00:09:20.867 --> 00:09:24.280
have the right to say all that.

00:09:24.280 --> 00:09:29.642
Do you, my little suns, think
that this Mass is valuable

00:09:29.642 --> 00:09:32.079
because the priest is good?

00:09:33.420 --> 00:09:38.029
Does this Eucharist matter because
the priest is devout, not a thief,

00:09:38.029 --> 00:09:40.333
doesn't drive a BMW, or whatever?

00:09:40.333 --> 00:09:46.095
And when you look at social media,
and Sunshine and I are with you on

00:09:46.095 --> 00:09:48.783
TikTok, I see the nonsense you watch.

00:09:48.783 --> 00:09:51.088
So, there are topics like this.

00:09:51.088 --> 00:09:53.008
Don't go to Mass, right?

00:09:53.008 --> 00:09:54.929
Tell me honestly, let's talk.

00:09:54.929 --> 00:10:01.075
Half of you are ashamed to say you go
to church at school, isn't that right?

00:10:01.915 --> 00:10:04.145
Who imposed that on you?

00:10:04.145 --> 00:10:08.160
Social media is an idol
that isn't for believers.

00:10:08.160 --> 00:10:11.729
And Jesus says, who are you conforming to?

00:10:11.729 --> 00:10:13.514
This world or Him.

00:10:13.514 --> 00:10:17.529
So, what is important for
you to understand now?

00:10:17.529 --> 00:10:22.882
That the Mass is so significant and
it always holds value, regardless

00:10:22.882 --> 00:10:27.343
of us priests, whether we are
interesting, boring, or whatever.

00:10:27.343 --> 00:10:28.236
Here's how.

00:10:28.236 --> 00:10:31.805
When did the Israelites
receive manna from heaven?

00:10:31.824 --> 00:10:33.286
When God fed them.

00:10:33.286 --> 00:10:35.114
Something always happened before that.

00:10:35.114 --> 00:10:40.230
Today, we had the election of the
Pope, and before the Pope was chosen,

00:10:40.230 --> 00:10:42.423
we all expected that white smoke.

00:10:42.423 --> 00:10:45.712
The Israelites, before God would
feed them, expected something

00:10:45.712 --> 00:10:50.098
as well; there was a sign that
manna would come from heaven.

00:10:50.098 --> 00:10:52.290
Do you know what it was?

00:10:52.290 --> 00:10:57.407
It says in the Holy Scripture that
there was always a heavy dew, gentle.

00:10:57.407 --> 00:10:59.600
Do you know what dew is?

00:10:59.840 --> 00:11:02.024
Like a gentle drizzle.

00:11:02.024 --> 00:11:08.579
So, there was always a sign that
manna, food from heaven, would

00:11:08.579 --> 00:11:12.403
descend, and that sign was the dew.

00:11:12.403 --> 00:11:18.957
Later, when Filip and I celebrate
Mass, listen carefully, we won't say

00:11:18.957 --> 00:11:27.151
"sanctify these gifts through us," but
both of us will say, "God, source of all

00:11:27.151 --> 00:11:30.975
holiness," and we will extend our hands.

00:11:31.185 --> 00:11:36.448
"Sanctify these gifts means we are
addressing God, just as in the Old

00:11:36.448 --> 00:11:42.522
Testament the source symbol of bread that
would come from heaven was dew, here in

00:11:42.522 --> 00:11:45.761
the New Testament it is the Holy Spirit.

00:11:45.761 --> 00:11:51.835
And that is why we will extend our
hand and say, 'God, source of all

00:11:51.835 --> 00:11:56.288
holiness, sanctify these gifts.'
And you see, the Eucharist is valid

00:11:56.288 --> 00:11:59.123
regardless of what the priests are like.

00:11:59.123 --> 00:12:01.957
Every sacrament is
valid, regardless of us.

00:12:01.957 --> 00:12:07.626
We need to be examples, but it should
not be your mantra and decision

00:12:07.626 --> 00:12:12.485
to stop going to church after
confirmation because of this or that."

00:12:12.485 --> 00:12:18.432
So we look for an excuse for our,
what is it called, I preached last

00:12:18.432 --> 00:12:22.793
Thursday, it's called, how the sun,
you who listened, spiritual laziness.

00:12:22.793 --> 00:12:27.551
Yes, that's why you need to
be aware of what is happening.

00:12:27.551 --> 00:12:34.687
If we do not eat the body and blood of
Christ, it means Jesus at the Last Supper

00:12:34.687 --> 00:12:41.031
did not say come when you are well-rested,
come if you don't have training, come if

00:12:41.031 --> 00:12:46.978
it doesn't rain, come if it's not sunny,
but Jesus explicitly says whoever eats and

00:12:46.978 --> 00:12:50.150
drinks my body and blood has eternal life.

00:12:50.150 --> 00:12:50.574
Point.

00:12:50.574 --> 00:12:52.270
Now, look at this.

00:12:52.270 --> 00:12:54.816
How do we behave at Mass?

00:12:54.816 --> 00:12:59.906
The first sign of how much we
believe that Jesus is truly

00:12:59.906 --> 00:13:02.451
present in that piece of bread.

00:13:02.451 --> 00:13:05.420
How many of you truly believe that?

00:13:05.420 --> 00:13:06.268
How many?

00:13:06.268 --> 00:13:12.207
See, there's no need to doubt, hesitate,
or be ashamed; it should be clear.

00:13:12.207 --> 00:13:13.055
I believe.

00:13:13.055 --> 00:13:16.025
But obviously, not all of us believe.

00:13:16.025 --> 00:13:21.963
It is said that a Muslim went to
Mass with his Catholic friend, and

00:13:21.963 --> 00:13:27.053
the Catholic tried to prepare him,
to explain what happens at Mass.

00:13:27.053 --> 00:13:32.144
He said, "We Christians believe
that this bread becomes the body of

00:13:32.144 --> 00:13:37.658
Christ, that this wine becomes the
blood of Christ," to give him some

00:13:37.658 --> 00:13:40.627
context about what we do at Mass.

00:13:40.627 --> 00:13:46.142
And now, this Muslim observed, the
Mass ended, and his friend asked him,

00:13:46.142 --> 00:13:51.656
"So, what do you think?" The Muslim
replied, "Listen, I don't believe that

00:13:51.656 --> 00:13:57.595
you believe that the bread and wine
become the body and blood of Christ."

00:13:58.555 --> 00:14:04.322
This person says, "Well, it's okay, you're
a Muslim, you were raised in a different

00:14:04.322 --> 00:14:09.321
faith, and that's completely normal."
But he says, "No, no, no, I misspoke.

00:14:09.321 --> 00:14:12.397
I don't believe that you
believers actually believe

00:14:12.397 --> 00:14:14.704
that this is the living God.

00:14:14.704 --> 00:14:18.933
Because if I, as a Muslim,
believed what you believe, I

00:14:18.933 --> 00:14:21.625
would kneel and not lift my head."

00:14:22.405 --> 00:14:23.459
Do you understand?

00:14:23.459 --> 00:14:25.919
I would kneel out of reverent fear.

00:14:25.919 --> 00:14:30.488
The first sign of how much we
believe in this is reverent fear.

00:14:30.488 --> 00:14:35.760
Reverent fear is not the same as being
afraid of something; it's a deep respect.

00:14:35.760 --> 00:14:41.383
You can see it when we take communion,
when we enter the church, how we kneel.

00:14:41.383 --> 00:14:47.709
Most of you come to Mass on Sundays, and
you know how my heart aches when I see

00:14:47.709 --> 00:14:53.683
people leaving in groups right after the
sign of the cross, as if they came to Mass

00:14:53.683 --> 00:14:59.306
just to check it off their list, to get
a plus so they can receive confirmation.

00:14:59.306 --> 00:15:03.172
It means you haven't understood,
because if you believed that the

00:15:03.172 --> 00:15:07.741
living God is there, you wouldn't
be running out of the church, you

00:15:07.741 --> 00:15:09.498
wouldn't skip church on Sundays.

00:15:09.498 --> 00:15:14.770
I know some of you are listening to
me now and looking at me blankly,

00:15:14.770 --> 00:15:17.933
and I know half of you won't be here.

00:15:17.933 --> 00:15:22.502
But I've seen with my own eyes what
happens on Sundays—talking, joking around.

00:15:22.502 --> 00:15:26.368
I understand your age, and I
understand that maybe you don't

00:15:26.368 --> 00:15:27.774
fully grasp what's happening.

00:15:27.774 --> 00:15:30.585
That's why I'm telling you, my dear ones.

00:15:30.585 --> 00:15:36.560
Another thing I like to emphasize is how
to know if this is truly the living God.

00:15:36.560 --> 00:15:40.777
It often happens here, not just
here but in churches, that Satanists

00:15:40.777 --> 00:15:42.535
steal and resell consecrated hosts.

00:15:43.095 --> 00:15:46.433
There was a price of
around one hundred euros.

00:15:46.433 --> 00:15:50.885
You know that at the Capitol you
have these Christian stores where

00:15:50.885 --> 00:15:57.563
you can buy in bulk, you can go and
buy a kilo of hosts, a bag of hosts.

00:15:57.563 --> 00:16:03.128
So then, my question is, why do those
who resell, steal hosts from the church,

00:16:03.128 --> 00:16:05.725
sell them to Satanists to desecrate them?

00:16:05.725 --> 00:16:09.064
Why don't they just pass
off these unconsecrated ones

00:16:09.064 --> 00:16:11.290
and make a lot more money?

00:16:12.090 --> 00:16:18.032
Why do they have to risk coming to
the church here when one of us might

00:16:18.032 --> 00:16:19.888
notice them stealing the hosts?

00:16:19.888 --> 00:16:23.602
We've stopped people before
and made them consume the host.

00:16:23.602 --> 00:16:28.059
Why don't they just go to
the store, buy them, and sell

00:16:28.059 --> 00:16:30.287
them every day, at least 506?

00:16:30.287 --> 00:16:32.887
Because they are not
blessed, not consecrated.

00:16:32.887 --> 00:16:33.630
Bravo, Sokola.

00:16:38.694 --> 00:16:39.058
Bravo.

00:16:39.058 --> 00:16:42.690
So, because it is not
consecrated, what does that mean?

00:16:42.690 --> 00:16:45.959
Satan, the devil, knows exactly
which one is consecrated.

00:16:45.959 --> 00:16:48.865
He is not afraid of an unconsecrated host.

00:16:48.865 --> 00:16:54.313
I'm not trying to scare you, you are
confirmands, but let me tell you, when

00:16:54.313 --> 00:16:59.761
my faith in the Blessed Sacrament grew,
that's when I saw that Jesus is alive.

00:16:59.761 --> 00:17:06.300
So, I was leading, there was a priest, and
I was still a layperson, not yet a priest.

00:17:08.200 --> 00:17:13.220
So, I went with him as an escort,
my first spiritual retreat.

00:17:13.220 --> 00:17:17.823
The priest had adoration and took
the Blessed Sacrament, like the

00:17:17.823 --> 00:17:22.007
adoration we have on Thursdays, and
blessed each person individually.

00:17:22.007 --> 00:17:27.446
And when he showed it to one woman,
she started throwing herself on

00:17:27.446 --> 00:17:29.120
the floor, screaming, yelling.

00:17:29.584 --> 00:17:31.230
So, that's a manifestation.

00:17:31.230 --> 00:17:36.988
If it were just ordinary bread, why would
that woman be throwing herself around?

00:17:36.988 --> 00:17:41.923
You see how Satan knows
what is holy, but we do not.

00:17:41.923 --> 00:17:48.092
Some of you might have been at
the DDV once when a woman here was

00:17:48.092 --> 00:17:52.617
possessed, and whenever someone starts
having reactions, we move them to

00:17:52.617 --> 00:17:55.084
the sacristy, which is this room.

00:17:55.084 --> 00:17:58.375
We don't see the altar from the sacristy.

00:17:58.375 --> 00:18:03.310
I remember well when I took the
Blessed Sacrament to bless and

00:18:03.310 --> 00:18:05.367
turned it towards the sacristy.

00:18:05.367 --> 00:18:09.480
She couldn't see what I
was doing, but Satan could.

00:18:09.960 --> 00:18:12.450
So she started having reactions.

00:18:12.450 --> 00:18:19.921
So I'm just telling you this, how Satan
believes in the Holy Eucharist, and we

00:18:19.921 --> 00:18:27.890
dismiss it so lightly, we don't respect
it, we can't be bothered, yet we want to

00:18:27.890 --> 00:18:30.879
be spiritually strong, to resist Satan.

00:18:30.879 --> 00:18:31.377
How?

00:18:31.377 --> 00:18:38.350
So, before the liberation of the Israeli
people began, the Angel of Death came,

00:18:38.350 --> 00:18:42.335
and do you know what God told them?

00:18:42.335 --> 00:18:47.284
You who anoint the doorposts
and place the sign of the lamb's

00:18:47.284 --> 00:18:49.758
blood, it will pass over you.

00:18:49.758 --> 00:18:55.944
We, Christians, when we drink the body
and blood of Christ, Satan flees from us.

00:18:55.944 --> 00:18:58.006
The devil flees from us.

00:18:58.006 --> 00:19:04.193
If in the Old Testament that was a
symbol of animal blood, imagine how much

00:19:04.193 --> 00:19:07.080
the blood of Jesus Christ protects us.

00:19:07.080 --> 00:19:13.266
That is why the Eucharist is so important,
so that the spirit of laziness does

00:19:13.266 --> 00:19:19.452
not catch you, so that your going to
Mass is not something your mom and

00:19:19.452 --> 00:19:26.051
dad have to push you to do with a
broom, but that a desire is awakened

00:19:26.051 --> 00:19:28.938
in you, that you discover it yourself.

00:19:28.938 --> 00:19:32.650
And look, the first reading
was about that Philip.

00:19:33.670 --> 00:19:35.931
At confirmation, what do you receive?

00:19:35.931 --> 00:19:36.308
Gifts.

00:19:36.308 --> 00:19:40.455
Recently, there have been many
articles online about how much money

00:19:40.455 --> 00:19:42.340
should be given for confirmation.

00:19:42.340 --> 00:19:46.110
You see how we've degraded the
reception of the sacrament.

00:19:46.110 --> 00:19:50.633
All the portals are now writing about
the confirmation season, asking how

00:19:50.633 --> 00:19:52.895
much money is appropriate to give.

00:19:52.895 --> 00:19:56.288
We've completely shifted the meaning
of confirmation to commercialism.

00:19:56.288 --> 00:20:00.058
You, my dears, don't even
know how to dress anymore.

00:20:00.058 --> 00:20:02.320
Thank God they invented these robes.

00:20:02.620 --> 00:20:04.887
That you are all uniform.

00:20:04.887 --> 00:20:08.516
It has become so commercialized,
the sacraments, confirmations,

00:20:08.516 --> 00:20:12.599
baptisms, and everything, that
the spiritual essence is lost.

00:20:12.599 --> 00:20:13.959
And that's dangerous.

00:20:13.959 --> 00:20:18.042
In today's first reading, a
certain Philip is mentioned.

00:20:18.042 --> 00:20:20.310
Not Father Philip, but Philip.

00:20:20.310 --> 00:20:26.206
And it says something to him, it
says, the Holy Spirit told him.

00:20:26.206 --> 00:20:29.835
It urged him to get up and go.

00:20:29.835 --> 00:20:31.649
What do you receive?

00:20:31.950 --> 00:20:35.098
The Seal of the Gift of the Holy Spirit.

00:20:35.098 --> 00:20:39.647
The Holy Spirit will be upon
you, and we will pray for you.

00:20:39.647 --> 00:20:43.495
That the Holy Spirit may inspire
you as He inspired Philip

00:20:43.495 --> 00:20:45.245
today to approach that pagan.

00:20:45.245 --> 00:20:49.793
And we will pray that the Holy
Spirit inspires you too, my dears.

00:20:49.793 --> 00:20:54.691
And if you stray from God and
fall into sin, do not give up.

00:20:54.691 --> 00:20:58.889
Your conscience, the Holy Spirit will
speak to you through your conscience.

00:20:59.265 --> 00:21:03.435
Do not give up on God and the church.

00:21:03.435 --> 00:21:07.141
Never be ashamed of Jesus,
anywhere or anytime.

00:21:07.141 --> 00:21:09.921
Everyone will disappoint you, my dears.

00:21:09.921 --> 00:21:13.628
Your best friends, love,
future, job, career, everything.

00:21:13.628 --> 00:21:15.945
Jesus has never disappointed anyone.

00:21:15.945 --> 00:21:21.968
How beautiful it is when you can,
like tonight, stay before the Blessed

00:21:21.968 --> 00:21:24.285
Sacrament and bathe your soul.

00:21:24.765 --> 00:21:29.810
Stay and let your tears flow, let
Jesus touch your wounds a little.

00:21:29.810 --> 00:21:35.243
I feel sorry, I know you are young,
but you are not so protected.

00:21:35.243 --> 00:21:41.064
Life has grazed you too, and I have
noticed how that age boundary has lowered.

00:21:41.064 --> 00:21:45.721
So, we are all exposed today to fears,
anxieties, sins, and everything.

00:21:45.721 --> 00:21:49.990
And then, never be afraid to
come before Jesus and kneel.

00:21:49.990 --> 00:21:54.241
And believe me, I know,
the living Jesus is here.

00:21:54.241 --> 00:21:58.492
Whenever the church is open,
wherever you pass by, pray.

00:21:58.492 --> 00:22:04.868
Even if you don't know anything, just
come, just come before Him and you will

00:22:04.868 --> 00:22:07.844
see how the meaning of faith changes.

00:22:07.844 --> 00:22:09.544
And what happens then?

00:22:09.544 --> 00:22:15.496
What happened to the eunuch in that first
reading I mentioned with Philip happens.

00:22:15.496 --> 00:22:20.172
The Holy Spirit prompted Philip
to approach the chariot and say,

00:22:20.172 --> 00:22:25.273
a high dignitary of Candace, the
queen of Ethiopia, was passing by.

00:22:25.273 --> 00:22:31.649
He lived at the court with the queen,
he had everything, but he was unhappy.

00:22:32.129 --> 00:22:36.172
How many Christians do we have
today who have everything but

00:22:36.172 --> 00:22:38.009
are unhappy, but are empty?

00:22:38.009 --> 00:22:42.787
And the Holy Spirit prompted Philip
to approach him and ask, "Do you

00:22:42.787 --> 00:22:47.932
understand what you are reading?" See
how important it is for you to understand

00:22:47.932 --> 00:22:50.137
what is happening in the sacrament.

00:22:50.137 --> 00:22:55.649
So Philip asks the eunuch, and he says,
"I don't know unless someone teaches me."

00:22:58.250 --> 00:23:02.227
And you see, that eunuch was
infertile, but he was religious.

00:23:02.227 --> 00:23:06.205
He was traveling because he was
on a pilgrimage to Jerusalem.

00:23:06.205 --> 00:23:11.268
He was doing things according to the
rules, but he still didn't feel anything.

00:23:11.268 --> 00:23:15.969
How many of us go on pilgrimages,
attend events, come here to DDV,

00:23:15.969 --> 00:23:18.501
but not all come because of God.

00:23:18.501 --> 00:23:23.564
Some come to find a girlfriend, some
because they are bored at home, some

00:23:23.564 --> 00:23:28.265
because they have no company, but thank
God, sometimes God turns that into

00:23:28.265 --> 00:23:30.435
something good and changes their attitude.

00:23:32.635 --> 00:23:36.077
Sometimes we are just religious,
but nothing burns within us.

00:23:36.077 --> 00:23:38.831
And then we need someone to teach us.

00:23:38.831 --> 00:23:42.963
The Holy Spirit is the one
who intercedes for all of us.

00:23:42.963 --> 00:23:48.127
And what I love most is what the Holy
Scripture says about the Holy Spirit.

00:23:48.127 --> 00:23:52.602
Jesus says, if I do not go, the
Advocate will not come—the Spirit

00:23:52.602 --> 00:23:56.389
of comfort, the Spirit of truth,
who will teach you everything.

00:23:56.389 --> 00:24:00.791
Here comes the sun, my dear, I would
love for the Holy Spirit to truly

00:24:00.791 --> 00:24:04.900
awaken that love and passion in you,
just as Philip awakened it in the

00:24:04.900 --> 00:24:08.421
Eunuch, so that you burn with it
because he was ultimately baptized.

00:24:08.421 --> 00:24:11.356
He was baptized in the
fire of the Holy Spirit.

00:24:11.356 --> 00:24:16.345
I hope that you too will be baptized on
Sunday, but with the true fire of the

00:24:16.345 --> 00:24:20.747
Holy Spirit, not just to go through the
confirmation, but for it to truly be

00:24:20.747 --> 00:24:23.095
a seal of your love for Jesus Christ.

00:24:23.095 --> 00:24:23.715
Amen.

